<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="421" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1681,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1681,1706]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[291,427,1681,1706]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
). Body length 8.0–9.0 mm. Upper margin of mystax rounded in frontal view, reaching antennal sockets, distance between mystax and antennal sockets longer than scape and pedicel combined. Postocular setae not abundant. Antenna dark brown, sometimes pedicel reddish. Thorax black. Anepisternum anterodorsally without hairs, postpronotal lobe with short hairs. Dorsocentral setae long, distinct, reaching transverse suture. Scutellum with short white setae. Hypopygium black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="424" pageId="4" pageNumber="421" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1681,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,420,1861,1886]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Description. Male.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[427,488,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Head</emphasis>
black. Face below antennal sockets narrow, 0.21–0.23 × as wide as head. Face with silvery tomentum. Antenna dark brown, sometimes pedicel reddish, scape and pedicel with some white bristles. Hairs and setae of head white. Upper margin of mystax rounded in frontal view, reaching antennal sockets, distance between mystax and antennal sockets longer than scape and pedicel combined (
<figureCitation box="[1064,1149,1969,1994]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Postocular setae few in number. Palpus black with long white hairs, but shorter than mystax.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis box="[199,280,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Thorax</emphasis>
black, postpronotal lobe in some 
<typeStatus box="[656,763,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">paratypes</typeStatus>
dark brown. Scutum with greyish tomentum and two darker lateral spots of tomentum and darker paramedian and median stripes, with few short white hairs. Postpronotal lobe with short hairs as on scutum. Anepisternum anterodorsally without hairs, one 
<typeStatus box="[1044,1140,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">paratype</typeStatus>
with 1–3 short hairs (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Dorsocentral setae long, distinct, reaching or even crossing transverse suture, supra-alar setae long, reaching transverse suture (
<figureCitation box="[354,484,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
). Scutellum on margin with 15 or less short scutellar white setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" box="[199,658,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis box="[199,266,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Wings</emphasis>
clear, iridescence, halteres yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis box="[199,252,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Legs</emphasis>
. Coxa black with grayish tomentum and white setae. Trochanter reddish, fore- and mid-femur black, hind femur dark brown, tibia brownish, paler than hind femur, tarsus black, femur and tibia with reddish spot with indistinct boundary. Leg with white hairs and setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis box="[199,305,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites black with greyish tomentum and short white hairs, some tergites posteriorly and laterally reddish, sternites paler than tergites. Tergites along median line with dark stripe without hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis box="[199,342,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Hypopygium</emphasis>
large, well visible, black with white hairs, slightly turned (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1181,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
). Gonostyle distinctly curved at a right angle at the apex, with few hairs (
<figureCitation box="[754,889,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,264,991,1014]" captionTargetBox="[360,1227,224,955]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,213,961]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Line drawings of male genitalia of Habropogon lehri sp. nov., holotype. 16, 17. Hypopygium, lateral (16) and dorsal (17) view. 18 – 20. The same gonocoxite in different views. 21. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847952/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Figs 16–20</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal apodeme shorter than endoaedeagal process (
<figureCitation box="[250,333,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,264,991,1014]" captionTargetBox="[360,1227,224,955]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,213,961]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Line drawings of male genitalia of Habropogon lehri sp. nov., holotype. 16, 17. Hypopygium, lateral (16) and dorsal (17) view. 18 – 20. The same gonocoxite in different views. 21. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847952/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" box="[199,658,655,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,655,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Body length</emphasis>
8.0–9.0 (
<typeStatus box="[448,548,655,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">holotype</typeStatus>
8.5) mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,692,717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Female.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[311,398,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 23. 22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[384,1207,1112,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,1104,1911]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 23. 22. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♀, paratype, lateral view. 23. Distribution of Habropogon species (based on the current material and Lehr 1960, Astakhov 2015)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847954/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Similar to male except hairs and setae more dense on postsutural scutum and scutellum, terminalia dark brown.
</paragraph>
